cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the decidability of a problem related to game theory and verification, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of multidimensional mean-payoff games and the mention of Hilbert's Tenth problem over rationals suggest that the paper could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with game theory, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of infinite-memory strategies and the mention of undecidability suggest that the paper could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the use of strategies and verification suggests that the paper could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
